  "instructions": [
    "Heat the ghee in a ceramic tagine over medium heat.",
    "Add the ginger and garlic and cook until fragrant, about 2 minutes.",
    "Add the pork shoulder and cook until browned on all sides, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the pineapple chunks, lemon juice, honey, sparkling water, floral water, dried mint, salt, black pepper, cinnamon, and cayenne pepper. Stir to combine.",
    "Bring the mixture to a simmer and cook, covered, until the pork is tender and the liquid has reduced slightly.",
    "Flamb\u00115 the mixture with a splash of vodka, if desired.",
    "Serve the tagine hot, garnished with additional fresh mint if desired.",
    "Let the dish rest for at least 10 minutes before serving to allow the flavors to meld.",
    "Serve immediately, garnished with edible flowers if desired.",
    "Refrigerate or freeze leftovers for later use."
